.TH "create_pnp_modalias" 9 "create_pnp_modalias" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
create_pnp_modalias \- Create hid/cid(s) string for modalias and uevent
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" create_pnp_modalias
.BI "(struct acpi_device *acpi_dev "  ","
.BI "char *modalias "  ","
.BI "int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "acpi_dev" 12
ACPI device object.
.IP "modalias" 12
Buffer to print into.
.IP "size" 12
Size of the buffer.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Creates hid/cid(s) string needed for modalias and uevent
e.g. on a device with hid:IBM0001 and cid:ACPI0001 you get:
char *modalias: "acpi:IBM0001:ACPI0001"
.SH "RETURN"
0: no _HID and no _CID
-EINVAL: output error
-ENOMEM: output is truncated
